				\begin{document}$$\hbox{Percentage destruction} = 100\frac{{(CC_i - CC_t)}}{{CC_i}}$$\end{document} where CCi is the initial colony count and CCt is the colony count after a time interval ‘ t’. Average percentage destruction was then calculated and plotted as a function of time of exposure for each of the configurations.
